Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! An absolute snorter from Shamar Joseph! A painful end to innings for Jaker Ali. Shamar bends his back and digs it in short. Gets a good height on it as it comes around chest height and it hurries the batter as well. Jaker Ali goes for the pull but gets rushed in his shot and gets himself into an awkward position. The ball brushes the shoulder of the bat and then goes on to hit Jaker on the left shoulder. It results in the ball lobbing behind the wicket. The keeper, Joshua Da Silva settles under it and takes a dolly. Jaker drops his bat as soon as the ball hits him on the left shoulder. He looks in some serious discomfort as he trudges off. Shamar has his second wicket. From 83/2, Bangladesh have slipped to 95/5.

The ball catches the shoulder of the bat and lobs tamely towards gully where the substitute fielder, Zakir Hasan does the rest. Rana smiles and gives a thumbs up to someone in the slip cordon, so, this was a clear plan to go short to Brathwaite. The Windies skipper goes for 39 (129). Hodge is asked to wait as the catch is referred upstairs. The third umpire looks at a couple of replays and he is satisfied that Das took it cleanly and at no point, did the ball touch the turf. Commentary: OUT! LBW! This looks dead straight and up goes the finger! Joshua Da Silva nods his head after he reviews. Has he got some bat on it? The front-on replay shows that the ball has hit the back pad first before going on to make contact with the inside edge. It is confirmed by UltraEdge. The Ball Tracking shows three reds with the ball hitting the leg stump. This was bowled flatter, on middle and leg, Joshua Da Silva misreads the length and goes back to a delivery he should have been on the front foot. He looks to clip it away on the leg side but misses and gets hit on the back leg. Taijul completes his 15th five-wicket haul in Test cricket. West Indies lose Da Silva at the score of 164.

Commentary: OUT! TIMBER! Nahid Rana wraps things up, and Bangladesh secure a famous victory! Staying around the wicket, Rana changes things up after a barrage of short balls and delivers pinpoint yorker on off and middle. Shamar Joseph, deep in his crease, clears his front leg and attempts a hoick across the line. Gets beaten on the inside edge and the ball crashes into the stumps. This seals a monumental win for Bangladesh - ending a 15-year wait for a Test victory in the Caribbean!
